  <h2> ReferralWire Platform </h2>
  
  <div class="container-fluid">
  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-md-8">
  
    <p>ReferralWire was founded to support peer-to-peer lead sharing between businesses. ReferralWire is a customizable horizontal app/platform features out-of-the-box features for brand owners to manage their partner program and build new referrals based incentive marketing mechanics. Brand owners deploy ReferralWire as a white labeled PRM solution to their partner network. </p>

    <p>ReferralWire is a multi-tenant Saas Platform delivered on a continous integration cycle so all our customers get best experience at the same time. Software has been built on Standards based technologies and delivered simultaneoulsy on Web & Mobile devices over a global cloud platform.</p> 

    </div>
    <div class="col-md-4">
    <img width="200px" src="/APIWeb/images/hub.png" alt="hub" class="img-circle"/>
    </div>
  </div>  
  </div>


  

  <p>Referralwire features a rich set of developer tools and APIs that help companies manage their partner program, and tightly integrate referral mechanics across their websites, communities, mobile and enterprise applications. </p>

  <p>Built on REST, JavaScript, and open web standards, ReferralWire empowers developers to build delightful user experiences that fit naturally within the flow of their site or app, while ensuring enterprise-hardened, secure management of your partner program. ReferralWire APIs can be accessed by both server-side and page-side developers, empowering companies to make the most of their technical resources.</p>

  <p>All of these developer tools come accompanied by rich documentation, resources, tutorials, quickstarter projects on GIT, and best practices for writing code. These tools are available to all ReferralWire customers inside of the ReferralWire Community.</p>

  <p>ReferralWire REST API is a server-side API that has been designed from the ground up to facilitate partner interactions across your site or app. APIs make it simple to pull ReferralWire data onto a web page or into a mobile site, using an API call to request from the resource as little or as much information as you desire. That’s because APIs supports customizable fields and search specifications. This approach limits the amount of REST calls you need to make to the ReferralWire server, optimizing performance and speed while still ensuring you provide users with all the context you desire when they interact with a ReferralWire Objects. Key Endpoints Found in APIs </p>
  <hr>
    <ui>
    <li> Members </li>
    <li> Organizations </li>
    <li> Connections </li>
    <li> Leaders </li>
    <li> Referrals and LeaderBoards </li>
    </ui>
  <hr>  
  <p>While the APIs provides a powerful interface for server-side developers, the JavaScript Software Development Kit (SDK) provides a robust toolset for page-side developers -- people on your team who utilize popular web development languages like JavaScript, CSS and HTML. These technologies are most often used to build Brannd Owner Partners that interest the end-users on your site or app. The JS SDK can be leveraged in any page-side developer environment, allowing your team to work with their preferred tools. For example, front-end MVC frameworks like backbone and angularJS or JavaScript templating frameworks like handlebars or mustache.js.</p>

  <p>Community Edition of our product has been deployed by a networking organization (STNConnect) facilitating face-to-face partnerships and peer-to-peer lead sharing between small businesses. This organizatoin is currently at 1300 members and growing rapidly. </p>

  <p> <strong>If you are a business develpment person, information upto this point would give you a pretty good picture on what ReferralWire is and how you can bring ReferralWire into your enterprise. If you have further questions, please give us call, we will be happy to assist you. </strong></p>

  <p> If you are an SI or a programmer, exploring to implement solutions or applications based on ReferralWire Platform, please contact us or the brand owner for a developer account. </p>
